        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 1:42PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northeast of Bison, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Douglas...                        Bison...
Waukomis...                       Fairmont...
Hayward...                        Covington...
Garber...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
